    {
      "id": "t51",
      "tag": "button",
      "text": "Should artists prioritize Apple Music over Spotify?"
    },
    {
      "id": "t52",
      "tag": "div",
      "text": "Distribute to both through a distributor. Apple Music pays more per stream, but Spotify's algorithms reach far more new listeners. Both contribute to total career income."
    },
    {
      "id": "t53",
      "tag": "button",
      "text": "Is Tidal worth it for artists?"
    },
    {
      "id": "t54",
      "tag": "div",
      "text": "Tidal pays the highest per-stream rate ($0.008–$0.013) but has a much smaller subscriber base. Total earnings from Tidal are typically modest for most independent artists."
    },
    {
      "id": "t55",
      "tag": "button",
      "text": "Do streaming rates change over time?"
    },
    {
      "id": "t56",
      "tag": "div",
      "text": "Yes — rates fluctuate as platform subscriber counts, ad revenue, and total stream volumes change. Spotify's effective rate has remained relatively stable at $0.003–$0.005 for several years."
    },
